          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">
          Russia’s strike on Sumy
</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/police-release-attack-scene-footage.png" alt="Police showed the first footage from the scene of the attack" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Police showed the first footage from the scene of the attack. Credits: Getty Images</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Ukraine encountered the deadliest attack on civilians this year, killing 35 and injuring 117 on Sunday. While no evidence was provided, Russia said that the double missile attack was directed towards a meeting of Ukrainian soldiers. Amid this, Zelenskyy has <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-15-04-2025-h1-1-invited-trump" target="_blank">invited Trump</a> to visit Sumy and meet the people before making any agreement with Russia.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          While Trump coined this attack a “mistake,” he did not elaborate on the details. Trump's special envoy to Ukraine asserted that Russia has crossed the line of decency. Parallely, world leaders have condemned the attack and called the attack “a serious war crime” and “a blatant disregard of international law.” EU foreign ministers <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-15-04-2025-h1-2-assembled-in-luxembourg" target="_blank">assembled in Luxembourg</a> to determine how to proceed.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Meanwhile, Russian state media say the deadly missile strike on Sumy is a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://www.themoscowtimes.com/2025/04/14/russian-state-tv-paints-deadly-sumy-attack-as-staged-provocation-a88714" target="_blank">“staged provocation”</a> that sabotages ceasefire talks. The Kremlin denied targeting civilians and blamed Ukraine’s air defenses for “hitting the wrong target.”</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
