        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Trade war side quest</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/xi-jinping-to-lam-meeting-beijing-great-hall.png" alt="Chinese President Xi Jinping and Vietnam's President To Lam shake hands at the Great Hall of the People in Beijing" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Chinese President Xi Jinping and Vietnam's President To Lam shake hands at the Great Hall of the People in Beijing. Credits: Andres Martinez Casares/Reuters</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">As Southeast Asia catches its breath from the suspended reciprocal tariffs, Xi Jinping has set on a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-15-04-2025-h2-3-diplomatic-tour" target="_blank">diplomatic tour</a> to Vietnam, Malaysia, and Cambodia to position itself as a stable partner. On Monday, he visited Vietnam and urged them to resist “unilateral bullying” and uphold open trade. He also assured that China’s market was always open to Vietnam and emphasized strengthening strategic focus. </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Vietnam’s Deputy PM Bui Thanh Son said they expect Xi Jinping to sign 40 agreements across sectors, including railways, agriculture, and green economy. Hanoi has already approved an $8.3B railway project linking Haiphong to China. Meanwhile, Vietnam has seen a surge in Chinese investments, with trade nearly doubling from 2014 to 2024. </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Wen-ti Sung, a non-resident fellow at the Atlantic Council, said China is looking to diversify its economic footprint worldwide and tries to pull countries closer amid Trump’s tariff scare.  </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Despite stronger economic ties, tensions remain between Southeast Asia and China, especially concerning the South China Sea. Xi stressed the need to manage differences and promote regional peace. </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="0px 12px" />
