        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">The indirect nuclear talk </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;"><strong>Summary: The US and Iran held their first bilateral talks in nearly seven years in Oman.</strong></p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          The first round of <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-15-04-2025-h3-4-indirect-talks" target="_blank">indirect talks</a> between US Special Envoy Steve Witkoff and Iran’s Foreign Minister Abbas Aragach has concluded. Aragach asserted that the discussions were constructive and held in a “calm and respectful environment.” Oman’s foreign minister acted as a mediator between them. 
        </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Witkoff mapped out an agenda similar to the 2015 nuclear agreement that will also address Iran’s increased stockpile of enriched uranium. Meanwhile, Iran said that the nuclear stockpile will be used for civil purposes.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The next round of talks on <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-15-04-2025-h3-5-april-19-in-muscat" target="_blank">April 19 in Muscat</a> will discuss safely dispensing the stockpile and reintroducing the independent inspection. The UN nuclear weapon inspectorate, the IAEA, asserted that Iran hadn’t turned on their camera, so they could not identify the on-ground works.  </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Critics believe the US and Iran have cleared a low bar, and a likely framework could be discussed. They also emphasized the negotiations' insulation from external forces and exercise restraint.</p>
        </mj-text>
