          <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
            <strong>🇪🇨 President Daniel Noboa reelected in Ecuador in a runoff election</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           Conservative President Daniel Noboa <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-15-04-2025-br1-6-defeated-left-wing" target="_blank">defeated left-wing</a> Luisa Gonzalez in Ecuador’s presidential runoff election by amassing 55.8% of the vote. Gonzalez, who had the backing of former President Rafael Correa, rejected the results. She called it “grotesque electoral fraud” and asked for a recount. 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Key issues for voters included surging drug violence, gang activity, and a struggling economy. Meanwhile, the homicide cases have slightly declined, though it remains high. Noboa declared an “internal armed conflict” in January 2024, which allowed military deployment to combat cartels. He was recently seeking US private mercenaries <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-15-04-2025-br1-7-to-combat-crime" target="_blank">to combat crime</a> in Ecuador.</p>
        </mj-text>
